# {project_name}

PyTorch-Vision QuinkGL peer scaffolded from the `{template}` template.

## Run the peer

```bash
pip install -e .
python -m peer_main
```

The canonical Mode C script (`peer_main.py`) loads `{manifest_filename}`,
constructs a `GossipNode`, and starts training.

## Test

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
pytest
```

`conftest.py` provides a `fake_swarm` fixture via `quinkgl.testing`.
`test_build_model.py` and `test_build_loaders.py` assert that the
script-level stubs raise `NotImplementedError` until implemented.
